{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Rev|8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","chapter":8,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":1,"text":"When he opened the seventh seal, there was silence in heaven for about half an hour.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":2,"text":"Then I saw the seven angels who stand in the presence of God; seven trumpets were given to them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":3,"text":"Another angel, with a golden incense burner, came and stood at the altar. He was given a large amount of incense to offer with the prayers of all the saints on the golden altar in front of the throne.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":4,"text":"The smoke of the incense, with the prayers of the saints, went up in the presence of God from the angel’s hand.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":5,"text":"The angel took the incense burner, filled it with fire from the altar, and hurled it to the earth; there were peals of thunder, rumblings, flashes of lightning, and an earthquake.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":6,"text":"And the seven angels who had the seven trumpets prepared to blow them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":7,"text":"The first angel blew his trumpet, and hail and fire, mixed with blood, were hurled to the earth. So a third of the earth was burned up, a third of the trees were burned up, and all the green grass was burned up.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":8,"text":"The second angel blew his trumpet, and something like a great mountain ablaze with fire was hurled into the sea. So a third of the sea became blood,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":9,"text":"a third of the living creatures in the sea died, and a third of the ships were destroyed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":10,"text":"The third angel blew his trumpet, and a great star, blazing like a torch, fell from heaven. It fell on a third of the rivers and springs of water.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":11,"text":"The name of the star is Wormwood, and a third of the waters became wormwood. So, many of the people died from the waters, because they had been made bitter.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":12,"text":"The fourth angel blew his trumpet, and a third of the sun was struck, a third of the moon, and a third of the stars, so that a third of them were darkened. A third of the day was without light and also a third of the night.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","bookOrder":65,"chapter":8,"verse":13,"text":"I looked and heard an eagle flying high overhead, crying out in a loud voice, “Woe! Woe! Woe to those who live on the earth, because of the remaining trumpet blasts that the three angels are about to sound!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rev","chapter":8,"paragraphStarts":[1,6,7,8,10,12,13],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"The Seventh Seal"},{"beforeVerse":6,"text":"The Seven Trumpets"},{"beforeVerse":7,"text":"The First Trumpet"},{"beforeVerse":8,"text":"The Second Trumpet"},{"beforeVerse":10,"text":"The Third Trumpet"},{"beforeVerse":12,"text":"The Fourth Trumpet"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When he opened the seventh seal, there was silence "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Hab 2:20","book":"Hab","chapter":2,"verse":20,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Zp 1:7","book":"Zep","chapter":1,"verse":7,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Zch 2:13","book":"Zec","chapter":2,"verse":13,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" in heaven for about half an hour. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Hab 2:20","book":"Hab","chapter":2,"verse":20},{"label":"Zp 1:7","book":"Zep","chapter":1,"verse":7},{"label":"Zch 2:13","book":"Zec","chapter":2,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rev:8:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then I saw the seven angels who stand in the presence of God; "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 1:19","book":"Luk","chapter":1,"verse":19,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 15:1","book":"Rev","chapter":15,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 15:6","book":"Rev","chapter":15,"verse":6,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 16:1","book":"Rev","chapter":16,"verse":1,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 17:1","book":"Rev","chapter":17,"verse":1,"letter"